Shiva: HMMER testsuite

#####################################################################
I. Compiled test drivers.
---------------------------------------------------------------------

- A test driver runs with no arguments, gives no output, 
  and returns EXIT_SUCCESS if the test passes.
- If the test fails, the test driver calls Die() to print a diagnostic on
  stderr, and exit with EXIT_FAILURE.
- The -v option always activates rudimentary verbose output on stdout.

Current tests:
---------------

evd_test.c           -- exercises code in histogram.c, especially EVD fitting
masks.c              -- exercises code in masks.c
tophits_test.c       -- exercises code in tophits.c
trace_test.c         -- exercises traceback code in core_algorithms.c
   trace_test.hmm        -- HMM used by trace_test.c
   trace_test.seq        -- test set used by trace_test.c
   trace_test.slx        -- alignment used to build trace_test.hmm





#####################################################################
Obsolete: kept in RCS archive only for reproducibility of old results
---------------------------------------------------------------------

fitting_test.c	Tests of EVD and Gaussian histogram fitting code.
		17 June 1997



#####################################################################
"Shiva" refers to Shiva the Destroyer, from Hindu mythology. Shiva
destroys to keep the world in balance. It seems an obvious name for
a test suite directory.

